Sentencing is expected on Wednesday in the Baby Daniel trial in the Johannesburg High Court. The three-year-old toddler died in June 2017 after being submerged in hot water and blunt force was applied to his head more than 10 times. Judge Joseph Matshitse found the mother Mary Vermaak guilty on two counts of child neglect and her partner and father of her two other children, Timothy Naidoo guilty of child abuse and murder. Listen for more: <a href="https://iono.fm/e/672449">Content hosted by iono.fm</a> 